Read mappings of variable regions to genes
For each methylation-variable region, we take overlapping or nearest genes.
For each accessibility-variable region, we take the nearest transcription start site.

methvr_gene_overlaps <- read_tsv("/mnt/volume/20-11-03_scNMT-SVZ2/analysis/21-11-10_genes-overlapping-methVRs.tsv.gz", show_col_types=F) %>% 
  group_by(region) %>%
  arrange(dist_tss, gene_id) %>% 
  slice_head(n=1) %>% 
  ungroup()
# methVR -> nearest gene
methvr_to_gene <- methvr_gene_overlaps %>% dplyr::select(region, gene_symbol) %>% deframe()
# gene -> nearest methVR
gene_to_methvr <- methvr_gene_overlaps %>% 
  group_by(gene_symbol) %>%
  arrange(dist_tss, gene_id) %>% 
  slice_head(n=1) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% dplyr::select(gene_symbol, region) %>% deframe()

bin the cells in pseudotime

cells_per_small_bin <- 10
cells_per_large_bin <- 19

tmp <- mofa_out %>%
  left_join(dplyr::select(integrated_df_10X, sample, predicted_ct), by="sample") %>% 
  mutate(bin_group = case_when(
    celltype_tissue == "oligodendrocyte" ~ "Oli",
    predicted_ct == "neuron" ~ "OBN",
    celltype_tissue == "neuroblast/neuron (OB)" ~ "OB",
    celltype_tissue == "astrocyte (striatum)" ~ "StrA",
    celltype_tissue == "qNSC1" ~ "A",
    sample %in% lineage_cells ~ "lin",
    TRUE ~ NA_character_
  )) %>%
  group_by(bin_group) %>% 
  mutate(n_bins = floor(n() / cells_per_small_bin),  # this ensures we get about 10-12 cells per bin
         n_bins_large = floor(n() / cells_per_large_bin)) %>%
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(n_bins = if_else(n_bins < 1, 1, n_bins),  # bins of size 0 don't make sense, need at least 1 bin
         n_bins_large = if_else(n_bins_large < 1, 1, n_bins_large))

# I don't know why cut_number doesn't worked on grouped variables... So I'm doing it manually
mofa_out_binned <- bind_rows(
  tmp %>%

color_default <- function(mat, direction=1L) {
  colors <- c("blue", "#EEEEEE", "red")
  if (direction < 0) {
    colors <- rev(colors)
  }
  q1  <- quantile(mat, .01, na.rm = TRUE)
  q99 <- quantile(mat, .99, na.rm = TRUE)
  circlize::colorRamp2(seq(q1, q99, length = 3), colors, space="LAB")
}

color_cw <- function(mat, direction=1L) {
  colors <- heatmaply::cool_warm(100)
  if (direction < 0) {
    colors <- rev(colors)
  }
  q1  <- quantile(mat, .01, na.rm = TRUE)
  q99 <- quantile(mat, .99, na.rm = TRUE)
  circlize::colorRamp2(seq(q1, q99, length = 100), colors, space="LAB")
}

color_viridis <- function(mat, ...) {
  colors <- viridisLite::viridis(100, ...)
  q1  <- quantile(mat, .01, na.rm = TRUE)
  q99 <- quantile(mat, .99, na.rm = TRUE)
  circlize::colorRamp2(seq(q1, q99, length = 100), colors, space="LAB")
}

color_ocean <- function(mat, direction=1L) {
  colors <- pals::ocean.balance(110)[6:105]
  if (direction < 0) {
    colors <- rev(colors)
  }
  q1  <- quantile(mat, .01, na.rm = TRUE)
  q99 <- quantile(mat, .99, na.rm = TRUE)
  circlize::colorRamp2(seq(q1, q99, length = 100), colors, space="LAB")
}
wilcox_test_gene <- function(mtx, feature_idx, cell_idx1, cell_idx2, pseudocount=1e-20, ...) {
  counts1 <- mtx[cell_idx1, feature_idx]
  counts2 <- mtx[cell_idx2, feature_idx]
  counts_full <- mtx[c(cell_idx1, cell_idx2), feature_idx]
  mean_expr <- mean(counts_full, na.rm=T)
  n_obs_rna <- sum(counts_full > 0, na.rm=T)
  p <- wilcox.test(counts1, counts2, ...)$p.value
  lfc <- log2(mean(counts1, na.rm=T) + pseudocount) - log2(mean(counts2, na.rm=T) + pseudocount)
  data.frame(p_rna = p, lfc_rna = lfc, mean_rna = mean_expr, n_obs_rna = n_obs_rna)
}

wilcox_test_rna <- function(fg_clusters, bg_clusters){
  fg_cells <- mofa_out %>% dplyr::filter(celltype_tissue %in% fg_clusters) %>% pull(sample)
  bg_cells <- mofa_out %>% dplyr::filter(celltype_tissue %in% bg_clusters) %>% pull(sample)

  message("running wilcox RNA")
  tibble(gene_symbol = genes_for_wilcox) %>% 
    rowwise() %>% 
    mutate(wilcox_test_gene(rna_mtx_lognorm, gene_symbol, fg_cells, bg_cells, exact=F)) %>% 
    ungroup() %>%
    mutate(padj_rna = p.adjust(p_rna, method="fdr"))
}

average_features <- function(mtx, bin_names, feature_names, cell_annot) {
  # average multiple genes (or other features) over a group of cells (e.g. cells binned in pseudotime)
  sapply(bin_names, function(clst) {
    cell_idx <- dplyr::filter(cell_annot, ptime_bin_large == clst) %>% pull(sample) %>% unique()
    colMeans(mtx[cell_idx, feature_names], na.rm=T)
    }) %>%
  colMeans(na.rm=T)
}

summary_matrix <- function(mtx, bin_names, gene_set_names, cell_annot, gene_annot, mode="gene") {
  # average multiple gene sets
  stopifnot(mode %in% c("gene", "region"))
  sapply(gene_set_names, function(gs) {
    if (mode == "gene") {
      features_in_set <- dplyr::filter(gene_annot, marker_celltype == gs) %>% pull(gene_symbol) %>% unique()
    } else if (mode == "region") {
      features_in_set <- dplyr::filter(gene_annot, marker_celltype == gs) %>% pull(region) %>% unique()
    }
    average_features(mtx, bin_names, features_in_set, cell_annot)
  })
}

plot_geneset_hm2 <- function(i, row_height=.5, cell_width=5, label=NULL, cscale_rows=T, cscale_cols=T, ...) {

  if (is.null(label)) {
    label <- paste(rownames(hm_mtx_rna)[i], "markers", sep=" ")
  }

  hm_rna <- hm_mtx_rna[i, , drop=F] %>%
    magrittr::set_rownames("gene expression") %>% 
    Heatmap(cluster_columns=F, cluster_rows=F, show_column_names=F, name="gene expression",
            column_split=hm_split_oli_large, column_title=c("", ""),
            width=unit(cell_width, "cm"), height=unit(row_height, "cm"), use_raster=F,
            col=color_viridis(hm_mtx_rna[cscale_rows, cscale_cols]),
            ...)
  
  hm_pm <- hm_mtx_prom_meth[i, , drop=F] %>%
    magrittr::set_rownames("promoter methylation") %>% 
    Heatmap(cluster_columns=F, cluster_rows=F, show_column_names=F, name="promoter methylation",
            column_split=hm_split_oli_large,
            width=unit(cell_width, "cm"), height=unit(row_height, "cm"), use_raster=F,
            col=color_viridis(hm_mtx_prom_meth[cscale_rows, cscale_cols], option="inferno", direction=-1L),
            ...)
  
  hm_pa <- hm_mtx_prom_acc[i, , drop=F] %>%
    magrittr::set_rownames("promoter accessibility") %>% 
    Heatmap(cluster_columns=F, cluster_rows=F, show_column_names=F, name="promoter accessibility",
            column_split=hm_split_oli_large,
            width=unit(cell_width, "cm"), height=unit(row_height, "cm"), use_raster=F,
            col=color_viridis(hm_mtx_prom_acc[cscale_rows, cscale_cols], option="cividis"),
            ...)
  
  hm_vm <- hm_mtx_vmr_meth[i, , drop=F] %>%
    magrittr::set_rownames("VMR methylation") %>% 
    Heatmap(cluster_columns=F, cluster_rows=F, show_column_names=F, name="VMR methylation",
            column_split=hm_split_oli_large,
            width=unit(cell_width, "cm"), height=unit(row_height, "cm"), use_raster=F,
            col=color_viridis(hm_mtx_vmr_meth[cscale_rows, cscale_cols], option="inferno", direction=-1L),
            ...)
  
  hm_va <- hm_mtx_vmr_acc[i, , drop=F] %>%
    magrittr::set_rownames("VMR accessibility") %>% 
    Heatmap(cluster_columns=F, cluster_rows=F, show_column_names=F, name="VMR accessibility",
            bottom_annotation=ha_oli_large, column_split=hm_split_oli_large,
            width=unit(cell_width, "cm"), height=unit(row_height, "cm"), use_raster=F,
            col=color_viridis(hm_mtx_vmr_acc[cscale_rows, cscale_cols], option="cividis"),
            ...)
  
  draw(hm_rna %v% hm_pm %v% hm_pa %v% hm_vm %v% hm_va,
       column_title = label, ht_gap = unit(c(.1, 0, .1, 0, .1), "cm"))
}

ssstep <- function(x, y, xs) {
  sum((mean(y[x <= xs]) - y[x <= xs])^2) + sum((mean(y[x > xs]) - y[x > xs])^2)
}

ssstep_ptime <- function(ptimes, feature, mtx) {
  meth_vals <- unname(mtx[lineage_cells_ordered, feature])
  non_na <- unname(!is.na(meth_vals))
  ptime_vals <- ptimes[non_na]

  if (sum(non_na) < 10) {
    return(NULL)        
  }

  tibble(
    ss = sapply(ptimes[non_na], function(st) ssstep(ptimes[non_na], meth_vals[non_na], st)),
    ptime = ptimes[non_na]
  )
}
cell_to_ptime <- mofa_out_binned %>%

ptimes <- unname(cell_to_ptime[lineage_cells_ordered])

get_direction <- function(region, min_ptime, mtx) {
  mean(mtx[lineage_cells_ordered[1:min_ptime], region], na.rm=T) > mean(mtx[lineage_cells_ordered[min_ptime:length(lineage_cells_ordered)], region], na.rm=T)
}

hm_colors <- function(percent_trim) {
  constant_n <- 1000 * percent_trim / 100
  scale_n <- 1000 * (100-percent_trim) / 100
  c(viridis(scale_n, option="rocket"), rep(viridis(scale_n, option="rocket")[scale_n], constant_n))
}
